Constructor Detail

FtpSource

public FtpSource(String host,
                 String username,
                 String password)
Instantiates a new FtpSource.

Parameters:
host - The host name (or IP) of the FTP server, as well as the directory path where the assets are contained. This host often should end in a slash (/) unless one has already been specified in the host and the remainder of the host name is a prefix to a set of assets.
username - The user name to use sign into the server.
password - The password to use to sign into the server.

getStream

public InputStream getStream(String request)
                      throws Exception
Description copied from interface: AssetSource
Returns an InputStream to the requested asset. If the asset doesn't exist in this source then an exception will be thrown or null will be returned depending on the implementation.

Parameters:
request - The request for the asset.
Returns:
The reference to InputStream containing the requested asset, or null if the request was invalid.
Throws:
Exception - An error occurred retrieving the asset from the source.
